The paper proposes a framework for learning customized models of deformable materials from sparse example surface trajectories. This involves optimization, control forces, and model inference, which are all related to computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of optimization and control forces also suggests that the paper could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions synthetic examples and data captured from real-world objects, which could indicate that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for model inference, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
